    ") Algorithm 1 RGD for PoLAR parameterized (4) Require: Learning rates η, γ; sample X 0 and Y 0 uniformly from St(m, r) and St(n, r), respectively. for t = 0,.",
    ", T -1 do Find Θ t via (5a) Obtain Riemannian gradients E t and F t Update X t+1 and Y t+1 with (5b) and (5c) end for",
    "In problem (3), the matrix to be factorized (or the target matrix of LoRA; see Appendix C.3) is denoted as A ∈ R m×n, and Z 1, Z 2 represent the LoRA weights.",
    "In light of the lowrank setting, r ≪ min{m, n} is assumed.",
    "Problem (3) has been widely adopted as a testbed for developing advanced optimization schemes for LoRA; see, e.g., Zhang and Pilanci (2024) or Li et al. (2025a)."
